Sentencas: Electrolyte-supported solid oxide cells are often used for steam electrolysis.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Advantages are high mechanical stability and a low degradation rate.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: The aim of this proof of concept study was to use a femtosecond laser to process the electrolyte of an electrolyte-supported solid oxide cell and evaluate the effect of this laser treatment on the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: The femtosecond laser treatment induces a macroscopic and a superimposed microscopic structure.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: It can be proven that the electrolyte remains gas tight and the electrochemical performance increases independently of the laser parameters.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: The initial area-specific resistance degradation during a constant current measurement of 200 h was reduced from 7.9% for a non-treated reference cell to 3.2% for one of the laser-treated cells.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Based on electrochemical impedance measurements, it was found that the high frequency resistance of the laser-treated cells was reduced by up to 20% with respect to the reference cell.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: The impedance spectra were evaluated by calculating the distribution of relaxation times, and in advance, a novel approach was used to approximate the gas concentration resistance, which was related to the test setup and not to the cell.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: It was found that the low frequency polarization resistance was increased for the laser-treated cells.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: In total, the area-specific resistance of the laser-treated cells was reduced by up to 14%.
Titulo: Femtosecond Laser-Induced Surface Modification of the Electrolyte in Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells
